<div id="review_402941801" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/402941801" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1710557-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1475336903p2/1710557.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/402941801?book_show_action=true">Aug 29, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/1710557-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1710557-amy?shelf=bookcrossing">bookcrossing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1710557-amy?shelf=taught-me-something">taught-me-something</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1710557-amy?shelf=good-but-made-me-sad">good-but-made-me-sad</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer402941801" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12779819879041245378">Mary Doria Russell has enchanted me with several of her books. When I started this, I was hoping to be enchanted. I actually put it aside for a bit, because it wasn&apos;t hitting the mark for me. But then, a few days later, the characters kept calling me, so I picked it up again, and was swept into a view of WWII of which I was embarrassingly ignorant. This was a beautifully written story of the plight of those Jews in Italy, either by birth or immigration/escape, and of the patriots who fought agai</span>
  <span id="freeText12779819879041245378" style="display:none">Mary Doria Russell has enchanted me with several of her books. When I started this, I was hoping to be enchanted. I actually put it aside for a bit, because it wasn't hitting the mark for me. But then, a few days later, the characters kept calling me, so I picked it up again, and was swept into a view of WWII of which I was embarrassingly ignorant. This was a beautifully written story of the plight of those Jews in Italy, either by birth or immigration/escape, and of the patriots who fought against the Nazis. Stories of love, hope , separation, horror, redemption, loss, all interwoven. This book taught me as well as captured me.Not an easy read, but an enlightening one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12779819879041245378" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


