<div id="review_1995260683" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1995260683" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17792052-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1454295058p2/17792052.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1995260683?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/17792052-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17792052-amy?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17792052-amy?shelf=world-war-two">world-war-two</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17792052-amy?shelf=goodreads-favorites">goodreads-favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17792052-amy?shelf=jewish">jewish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17792052-amy?shelf=italy">italy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1995260683" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7133545637971714936">Thread of Grace was beautifully done. Written in 2004, it was my very first book by Mary Doria Russell, who it appears many of my Goodreads friends have loved and held in quite high esteem. Thread of Grace traces five families and some remarkable characters through the Nazi invasion of Italy, where German soldiers were looking to expunge and exterminate Jewish refugees, and anyone who tried to help them. I have read countless books on world war two, and never have I seen it from the Italian pers</span>
  <span id="freeText7133545637971714936" style="display:none">Thread of Grace was beautifully done. Written in 2004, it was my very first book by Mary Doria Russell, who it appears many of my Goodreads friends have loved and held in quite high esteem. Thread of Grace traces five families and some remarkable characters through the Nazi invasion of Italy, where German soldiers were looking to expunge and exterminate Jewish refugees, and anyone who tried to help them. I have read countless books on world war two, and never have I seen it from the Italian perspective and I found it really interesting. The character of Renzo, and also Mirella, they are both unforgettable. As is Lorenzo's mother Lidia, and Iacopo, the Rabbi. Fascinating responses, heroisms as well as fear, flight, and terror. It was beautifully done, and the story held my attention. The characters warm your heart and make you want to root for them. There was a bit of humor somehow, and a bit of every day interaction - that made the extraordinary tale somehow believable. Very glad this monthly tag allowed me to read something I wouldn't have necessarily picked up. Its also book Six for stair 5 - Historical Fiction. Plus, I happened to own this book, and its about the 20th I've read in 2017 that I own, so I feel I am clearing some of the shelves. This one I will leave in the little library for someone to pick up and enjoy. Not a bad pick for 2004 - it was a fabulous one!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7133545637971714936" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


