<div id="review_3176782635" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3176782635" />
    <a title="Elizabeth☮ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/990216-elizabeth"><img alt="Elizabeth☮ " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528771086p2/990216.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3176782635?book_show_action=true">Feb 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth☮ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth☮ " href="/user/show/990216-elizabeth">Elizabeth☮ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780375501845" href="/book/show/896840.A_Thread_of_Grace">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/990216-elizabeth?shelf=recent-reads">recent-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/990216-elizabeth?shelf=recommended-books">recommended-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3176782635" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11580539477403997679">This is a look at Italy&apos;s involvement in WWII. More specifically, how the Catholic church and the every day farmers helped hide Jewish men, women and children during the final push of the German military into Italy after the fall of Mussolini. <br/><br/>Russell offers a cast of characters in the front of the book which is helpful to keep all of the characters straight. The one character that ties all of the threads of the story together is Renzo, a former military man, that takes on various personas in th</span>
  <span id="freeText11580539477403997679" style="display:none">This is a look at Italy's involvement in WWII. More specifically, how the Catholic church and the every day farmers helped hide Jewish men, women and children during the final push of the German military into Italy after the fall of Mussolini. <br /><br />Russell offers a cast of characters in the front of the book which is helpful to keep all of the characters straight. The one character that ties all of the threads of the story together is Renzo, a former military man, that takes on various personas in the course of the book. You get to know him and all of those around him in a manner that feels real and meaningful.<br /><br />The mind of Russell is amazing because she pulls together several threads that makes sense in the end. The title references a saying that indicates no matter the challenges God gives you, there is always a thread of grace. I think the way Russell tells the story for all of the faceless men and women that sacrificed, in many instances, their own safety, she illustrates the grace of humanity. So good.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11580539477403997679" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


